129.8	Miguel_de_Cervantes	Miguel de Cervantes	Miguel de Cervantes Saavedra (Spanish pronunciation: ; (Born 1547 (day unknown); died 22 April 1616) was a Spanish novelist, poet, and playwright. His magnum opus, Don Quixote, considered the first modern European novel, is a classic of Western literature, and is regarded amongst the best works of fiction ever written. His influence on the Spanish language has been so great that the language is often called la lengua de Cervantes ("the language of Cervantes"). He was dubbed El Pr√≠ncipe de los Ingenios ("The Prince of Wits").	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/66/Cervates_jauregui.jpg/220px-Cervates_jauregui.jpg
